  "response": "The word \"wretched\" is often used to describe something or someone in a very poor, unfortunate, or miserable condition. Here are a few examples of how it can be used in a sentence:\n\n1. After the storm destroyed their home, the family was left in wretched conditions.\n2. She felt wretched after the argument, realizing she had said things she didn't mean.\n3. The stray dog looked so wretched and hungry that the couple decided to take it in and care for it.\n4. Despite his wretched circumstances, he managed to maintain a positive attitude.\n5. The wretched crime shocked the entire community.",
